-- Raul Gonzalez, Guti Poised to Leave Real Madrid, Sky Sports Reports
-- Peter-Joseph Hegarty
-- 2010-07-25T19:15:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-25/raul-gonzalez-guti-poised-to-leave-real-madrid-sky-sports-reports.html

          
          
             Former Spain striker Raul Gonzalez
will bid farewell to nine-time European soccer champion Real
Madrid tomorrow, Sky Sports reported. He’s been linked in media
reports with Germany’s Schalke.  
 Raul, 33, made his debut in 1994-95 and helped Real to win
three Champions League titles. He’s the all-time top scorer in
the competition.  
 Today, Real midfielder Guti announced his departure
and is set to join Turkish team Besiktas, Sky reported.  
          
          


  


        